#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression editor is an editor for editing regular expression in "
"a graphical style (in contrast to the <acronym>ASCII</acronym> syntax). "
"Traditionally regular expressions have been typed in the <acronym>ASCII</"
"acronym> syntax, which for example looks like <literal>^.*kde\\b</literal>. "
"The major drawbacks of this style are:"
msgstr ""
"Urejevalnik regularnih izrazov je urejevalnik za urejanje regularnih izrazov "
"v grafičnem slogu (v nasprotju s sintakso <acronym>ASCII</acronym>). "
"Običajno so regularni izrazi vneseni v sintakso <acronym>ASCII</acronym>, ki "
"je na primer videti kot <literal>^.*kde\\b</literal>. Glavne pomanjkljivosti "
"tega sloga so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is hard to understand for non-programmers."
msgstr "Neprogramerjem je to težko razumeti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It requires that you <emphasis>escape</emphasis> certain symbols (to match a "
"star for example, you need to type <literal>\\*</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Zahteva, da <emphasis>dodajate ubežne simbole</emphasis> določenim simbolom "
"(če se na primer ujema z zvezdico, morate vnesti <literal>\\*</literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It requires that you remember rules for <emphasis>precedence</emphasis> "
"(What does <literal>x|y*</literal> match? a single <literal>x</literal> or a "
"number of <literal>y</literal>, <emphasis>OR</emphasis> a number of "
"<literal>x</literal> and <literal>y</literal>'s mixed?)"
msgstr ""
"Zahteva, da si zapomnite pravila za <emphasis>prednosti</emphasis> (Kaj se "
"ujema <literal>x|y*</literal>? en sam <literal>x</literal> ali število "
"<literal>y</literal>, <emphasis>ALI</emphasis> mešano število <literal>x</"
"literal> in <literal>y</literal>?)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression editor, on the other hand, lets you <emphasis>draw</"
"emphasis> your regular expression in an unambiguous way. The editor solves "
"at least item two and three above. It might not make regular expressions "
"available for the non-programmers, though only tests by users can tell that. "
"So, if are you a non programmer, who has gained the power of regular "
"expression from this editor, then please <ulink url=\"mailto:blackie@kde.org"
"\">let me know</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Po drugi strani pa vam urejevalnik regularnih izrazov omogoča "
"<emphasis>risanje</emphasis> regularnega izraza na nedvoumen način. "
"Urejevalnik reši vsaj dve in tri zgornje točke. Neprogramerjem morda ne bo "
"dal na voljo regularnih izrazov, čeprav lahko to ugotovijo le preizkusi "
"uporabnikov. Torej, če niste programer in ste pridobili moč regularnega "
"izražanja s tem urejevalnikom, potem <ulink url=\"mailto:blackie@kde.org"
"\">me obvestite</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is a Regular Expression"
msgstr "Kaj je regularni izraz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A regular expression is a way to specify <emphasis>conditions</emphasis> to "
"be fulfilled for a situation in mind. Normally when you search in a text "
"editor you specify the text to search for <emphasis>literally</emphasis>, "
"using a regular expression, on the other hand, you tell what a given match "
"would look like. Examples of this include <emphasis>I'm searching for the "
"word &kde;, but only at the beginning of the line</emphasis>, or "
"<emphasis>I'm searching for the word <literal>the</literal>, but it must "
"stand on its own</emphasis>, or <emphasis>I'm searching for files starting "
"with the word <literal>test</literal>, followed by a number of digits, for "
"example <literal>test12</literal>, <literal>test107</literal> and "
"<literal>test007</literal></emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"Regularni izraz je način za določitev <emphasis>pogojev</emphasis>, ki "
"morajo biti izpolnjeni za določeno situacijo. Običajno, ko iščete v "
"urejevalniku besedil, določite besedilo za iskanje <emphasis>dobesedno</"
"emphasis>, z uporabo regularnega izraza, po drugi strani pa poveste, kako bi "
"bilo videti dano ujemanje. Primeri tega vključujejo <emphasis>Iščem besedo "
"&kde; a samo na začetku vrstice</emphasis>, ali <emphasis>Iščem besedo "
"<literal>the</literal>, a mora stati samostojno</emphasis>, ali "
"<emphasis>Iščem datoteke, ki se začnejo z besedo <literal>test</literal>, ki "
"ji sledi več števk, na primer <literal>test12</literal>, <literal>test107</"
"literal> in <literal>test007</literal></emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You build regular expressions from smaller regular expressions, just like "
"you build large Lego toys from smaller subparts. As in the Lego world, there "
"are a number of basic building blocks. In the following I will describe each "
"of these basic building blocks using a number of examples."
msgstr ""
"Regularne izraze sestavljate iz manjših regularnih izrazov, tako kot "
"sestavljate velike igrače Lego iz manjših poddelov. Tako kot v Lego svetu "
"obstaja več osnovnih gradnikov. V nadaljevanju bom s številnimi primeri "
"opisal vsakega od teh osnovnih gradnikov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching for normal text."
msgstr "Iskanje običajnega besedila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you just want to search for a given text, then regular expression is "
"definitely not a good choice. The reason for this is that regular "
"expressions assign special meaning to some characters. This includes the "
"following characters: <literal>.*|$</literal>. Thus if you want to search "
"for the text <literal>kde.</literal> (i.e. the characters <literal>kde</"
"literal> followed by a period), then you would need to specify this as "
"<literal>kde\\.</literal><footnote><para>The regular expression editor "
"solves this problem by taking care of escape rules for you.</para></"
"footnote> Writing <literal>\\.</literal> rather than just <literal>.</"
"literal> is called <emphasis>escaping</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite samo iskati dano besedilo, regularni izraz zagotovo ni dobra "
"izbira. Razlog za to je, da regularni izrazi nekaterim znakom pripisujejo "
"poseben pomen. To vključuje naslednje znake: <literal>.*|$</literal>. Če "
"torej želite iskati besedilo <literal>kde.</literal> (tj. znake "
"<literal>kde</literal>, ki jim sledi pika), morate to podati kot <literal>kde"
"\\ .</literal><footnote><para>Urejevalnik regularnih izrazov reši to težavo "
"tako, da namesto vas poskrbi za ubežna pravila.</para></footnote> Pisanje "
"<literal>\\.</literal> namesto samo <literal>.</literal> se imenuje "
"<emphasis>izbegavanje (escaping)</emphasis>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching &URL;s"
msgstr "Ujemanje &URL;jev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select something looking like a &URL; in &kde;, then the program "
"<command>klipper</command> will offer to start <command>konqueror</command> "
"with the selected &URL;."
msgstr ""
"Ko izberete nekaj, kar je videti kot &URL; v &kde;, bo program "
"<command>klipper</command> ponudil zagon <command>konqueror</command> z "
"izbranim &URL;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>Klipper</command> does this by matching the selection against "
"several different regular expressions, when one of the regular expressions "
"matches, the accommodating command will be offered."
msgstr ""
"<command>Klipper</command> to naredi tako, da izbor primerja z več "
"različnimi regularnimi izrazi; ko se eden od regularnih izrazov ujema, bo "
"ponujen prilagojen ukaz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression for &URL;s says (among other things), that the "
"selection must start with the text <literal>http://</literal>. This is "
"described using regular expressions by prefixing the text <literal>http://</"
"literal> with a hat (the <literal>^</literal> character)."
msgstr ""
"Regularni izraz za &URL;s pravi (med drugim), da se mora izbor začeti z "
"besedilom <literal>http://</literal>. To je opisano z uporabo regularnih "
"izrazov s predpono besedila <literal>http://</literal> s klobukom (znak "
"<literal>^</literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above is an example of matching positions using regular expressions. "
"Similar, the position <emphasis>end-of-line</emphasis> can be matched using "
"the character <literal>$</literal> (i.e. a dollar sign)."
msgstr ""
"Zgoraj je primer ujemanja položajev z uporabo regularnih izrazov. Podobno se "
"lahko položaj <emphasis>konec vrstice</emphasis> ujema z uporabo znaka "
"<literal>$</literal> (tj. znak za dolar)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Searching for the word <literal>the</literal>, but not <emphasis>the</"
"emphasis><literal>re</literal>, <literal>brea</literal><emphasis>the</"
"emphasis> or <literal>ano</literal><emphasis>the</emphasis><literal>r</"
"literal>"
msgstr ""
"Iskanje besede <literal>the</literal>, vendar ne <emphasis>the</"
"emphasis><literal>re</literal>, <literal>brea</literal><emphasis>the</"
"emphasis> ali <literal>ano</literal><emphasis>the</emphasis><literal>r</"
"literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two extra position types can be matches in the above way, namely "
"<emphasis>the position at a word boundary</emphasis>, and <emphasis>the "
"position at a <emphasis>non</emphasis>-word boundary</emphasis>. The "
"positions are specified using the text <literal>\\b</literal> (for word-"
"boundary) and <literal>\\B</literal> (for non-word boundary)"
msgstr ""
"Na zgornji način je mogoče ujemati dve dodatni vrsti položaja, in sicer "
"<emphasis>položaj na besedni meji</emphasis> in <emphasis>položaj na "
"<emphasis>ne</emphasis>besedni meji</emphasis>. Položaji so podani z "
"besedilom <literal>\\b</literal> (za besedno mejo) in <literal>\\B</literal> "
"(za nebesedno mejo)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Thus, searching for the word <literal>the</literal> can be done using the "
"regular expression <literal>\\bthe\\b</literal>. This specifies that we are "
"searching for <literal>the</literal> with no letters on each side of it (i."
"e. with a word boundary on each side)"
msgstr ""
"Tako je iskanje besede <literal>the</literal> mogoče izvesti z regularnim "
"izrazom <literal>\\bthe\\b</literal>. To določa, da iščemo <literal>the</"
"literal> brez črk na vsaki strani (tj. z besedno mejo na vsaki strani)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The four position matching regular expressions are inserted in the regular "
"expression editor using <link linkend=\"positiontool\">four different "
"positions tool</link>"
msgstr ""
"Regularni izrazi, ki se ujemajo s štirimi položaji, so vstavljeni v "
"urejevalnik regularnih izrazov z <link linkend=\"positiontool\">orodjem za "
"štiri različne položaje</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching for either <literal>this</literal> or <literal>that</literal>"
msgstr "Iskanje <literal>this</literal> ali <literal>that</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine that you want to run through your document searching for either the "
"word <literal>this</literal> or the word <literal>that</literal>. With a "
"normal search method you could do this in two sweeps, the first time around, "
"you would search for <literal>this</literal>, and the second time around you "
"would search for <literal>that</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Predstavljajte si, da želite pregledati svoj dokument in iskati besedo "
"<literal>this</literal> ali besedo <literal>that</literal>. Z običajnim "
"načinom iskanja bi lahko to naredili v dveh poteh, pri čemer bi prvič iskali "
"<literal>this</literal>, drugič pa <literal>that</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using regular expression searches you would search for both in the same "
"sweep. You do this by searching for <literal>this|that</literal>, &ie; "
"separating the two words with a vertical bar."
msgstr ""
"Z iskanjem po regularnih izrazih bi istočasno iskali oboje. To storite tako, "
"da poiščete <literal>this|that</literal>, &ie; obe besedi ločite z navpično "
"črto."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note on each side of the vertical bar is a regular expression, so this "
"feature is not only for searching for two different pieces of text, but for "
"searching for two different regular expressions."
msgstr ""
"Opomba na vsaki strani navpične vrstice je regularni izraz, zato ta funkcija "
"ni samo za iskanje dveh različnih kosov besedila, ampak za iskanje dveh "
"različnih regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the regular expression editor you do not write the vertical bar yourself, "
"but instead select the <link linkend=\"altntool\">alternative tool</link>, "
"and insert the smaller regular expressions above each other."
msgstr ""
"V urejevalniku regularnih izrazov sami ne pišete navpične vrstice, temveč "
"namesto tega izberete <link linkend=\"altntool\">alternativno orodje</link> "
"in vstavite manjše regularne izraze enega nad drugega."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching anything"
msgstr "Ujemanje karkoli"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expressions are often compared to wildcard matching in the shell - "
"that is the capability to specify a number of files using the asterisk. You "
"will most likely recognize wildcard matching from the following examples:"
msgstr ""
"Regularni izrazi se pogosto primerjajo z ujemanjem nadomestnih znakov v "
"ukazni lupini - to je zmožnost določitve števila datotek z zvezdico. "
"Ujemanje nadomestnih znakov boste najverjetneje prepoznali iz naslednjih "
"primerov:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>ls *.txt</literal> - here <literal>*.txt</literal> is the shell "
"wildcard matching every file ending with the <literal>.txt</literal> "
"extension."
msgstr ""
"<literal>ls *.txt</literal> – tukaj je <literal>*.txt</literal> nadomestni "
"znak lupine, ki se ujema z vsako datoteko, ki se konča s pripono <literal>."
"txt</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>cat test??.res</literal> - matching every file starting with "
"<literal>test</literal> followed by two arbitrary characters, and finally "
"followed by the test <literal>.res</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>cat test??.res</literal> - ujemanje vsake datoteke, ki se začne z "
"<literal>test</literal>, ki ji sledita dva poljubna znaka, na koncu pa sledi "
"test <literal>.res</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the shell the asterisk matches any character any number of times. In "
"other words, the asterisk matches <emphasis>anything</emphasis>. This is "
"written like <literal>.*</literal> with regular expression syntax. The dot "
"matches any single character, &ie; just <emphasis>one</emphasis> character, "
"and the asterisk, says that the regular expression prior to it should be "
"matched any number of times. Together this says any single character any "
"number of times."
msgstr ""
"V lupini se zvezdica poljubno število ujema s katerim koli znakom. Z drugimi "
"besedami, zvezdica se ujema z <emphasis>karkoli</emphasis>. To je zapisano "
"kot <literal>.*</literal> s sintakso regularnega izraza. Pika se ujema s "
"katerim koli posameznim znakom, &ie;. samo <emphasis>en</emphasis> znak in "
"zvezdica pravi, da se mora regularni izraz pred njim ujemati poljubno "
"število krat. Skupaj to pove kateri koli posamezen znak poljubno število "
"krat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This may seem overly complicated, but when you get the larger picture you "
"will see the power. Let me show you another basic regular expression: "
"<literal>a</literal>. The letter <literal>a</literal> on its own is a "
"regular expression that matches a single letter, namely the letter "
"<literal>a</literal>. If we combine this with the asterisk, &ie; "
"<literal>a*</literal>, then we have a regular expression matching any number "
"of a's."
msgstr ""
"To se morda zdi preveč zapleteno, a ko boste dobili širšo sliko, boste "
"videli moč. Naj vam pokažem še en osnovni regularni izraz: <literal>a</"
"literal>. Črka <literal>a</literal> je sama po sebi regularni izraz, ki se "
"ujema z eno samo črko, in sicer črko <literal>a</literal>. Če to združimo z "
"zvezdico, &ie; <literal>a*</literal>, potem imamo regularni izraz, ki se "
"ujema s poljubnim številom a-jev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We can combine several regular expression after each other, for example "
"<literal>ba(na)*</literal>. <footnote><para><literal>(na)*</literal> just "
"says that what is inside the parenthesis is repeated any number of times.</"
"para></footnote> Imagine you had typed this regular expression into the "
"search field in a text editor, then you would have found the following words "
"(among others): <literal>ba</literal>, <literal>bana</literal>, "
"<literal>banana</literal>, <literal>bananananananana</literal>"
msgstr ""
"Lahko kombiniramo več regularnih izrazov enega za drugim, na primer "
"<literal>ba(na)*</literal>. <footnote><para><literal>(na)*</literal> samo "
"pravi, da se tisto, kar je v oklepaju, ponovi poljubno število krat.</para></"
"footnote> Predstavljajte si, da ste ta regularni izraz vnesli v iskanje "
"polje v urejevalniku besedila, potem bi našli naslednje besede (med drugim): "
"<literal>ba</literal>, <literal>bana</literal>, <literal>banana</literal>, "
"<literal>bananananananana </literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Given the information above, it hopefully isn't hard for you to write the "
"shell wildcard <literal>test??.res</literal> as a regular expression. "
"Answer: <literal>test..\\.res</literal>. The dot on its own is any "
"character. To match a single dot you must write <literal>\\.</"
"literal><footnote><para>This is called escaping</para></footnote>. In other "
"word, the regular expression <literal>\\.</literal> matches a dot, while a "
"dot on its own matches any character."
msgstr ""
"Glede na zgornje informacije upajmo, da vam ni težko napisati nadomestnega "
"znaka lupine <literal>test??.res</literal> kot regularni izraz. Odgovor: "
"<literal>test..\\.res</literal>. Pika sama po sebi je kateri koli znak. Za "
"ujemanje z eno samo piko morate napisati <literal>\\.</"
"literal><footnote><para>To se imenuje escaping</para></footnote>. Z drugimi "
"besedami, regularni izraz <literal>\\.</literal> se ujema s piko, medtem ko "
"se pika sama ujema s katerim koli znakom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the regular expression editor, a repeated regular expression is created "
"using the <link linkend=\"repeattool\">repeat tool</link>"
msgstr ""
"V urejevalniku regularnih izrazov se ponovljeni regularni izraz ustvari z "
"<link linkend=\"repeattool\">orodjem za ponavljanje</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replacing <literal>&amp;</literal> with <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> in a "
"&HTML; document"
msgstr ""
"Zamenjava <literal>&amp;</literal> z <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> v datoteki "
"&HTML; dokument"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &HTML; the special character <literal>&amp;</literal> must be written as "
"<literal>&amp;amp;</literal> - this is similar to escaping in regular "
"expressions."
msgstr ""
"V &HTML; posebni znak <literal>&amp;</literal> mora biti zapisan kot "
"<literal>&amp;amp;</literal> - to je podobno escapingu v regularnih izrazih."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine that you have written an &HTML; document in a normal editor (e.g. "
"&XEmacs; or &kate;), and you totally forgot about this rule. What you would "
"do when realized your mistake was to replace every occurrences of "
"<literal>&amp;</literal> with <literal>&amp;amp;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Predstavljajte si, da ste napisali &HTML; dokument v običajnem urejevalniku "
"(npr. &XEmacs; ali &kate;), in ste popolnoma pozabili na to pravilo. Kar bi "
"storili, ko bi spoznali svojo napako, je, da bi zamenjali vse pojavitve "
"<literal>&amp;</literal> z <literal>&amp;amp;</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can easily be done using normal search and replace, there is, however, "
"one glitch. Imagine that you did remember this rule - <emphasis>just a bit</"
"emphasis> - and did it right in some places. Replacing unconditionally would "
"result in <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> being replaced with <literal>&amp;amp;"
"amp;</literal>"
msgstr ""
"To je enostavno narediti z običajnim iskanjem in zamenjavo, vendar obstaja "
"ena napaka. Predstavljajte si, da ste si zapomnili to pravilo - "
"<emphasis>samo malo</emphasis> - in na nekaterih mestih naredili prav. "
"Brezpogojna zamenjava bi povzročila zamenjavo <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> z "
"<literal>&amp;amp;amp;</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What you really want to say is that <literal>&amp;</literal> should only be "
"replaced if it is <emphasis>not</emphasis> followed by the letters "
"<literal>amp;</literal>. You can do this using regular expressions using "
"<emphasis>positive lookahead</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Resnično želite povedati, da je treba <literal>&amp;</literal> zamenjati le, "
"če mu <emphasis>ne</emphasis> sledijo črke <literal>amp;</literal>. To lahko "
"storite z uporabo regularnih izrazov z <emphasis>pozitivnim pogledom vnaprej "
"(lookahead)</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression, which only matches an ampersand if it is not "
"followed by the letters <literal>amp;</literal> looks as follows: "
"<literal>&amp;(?!amp;)</literal>. This is, of course, easier to read using "
"the regular expression editor, where you would use the <link linkend="
"\"lookaheadtools\">lookahead tools</link>."
msgstr ""
"Regularni izraz, ki se ujema z ampersandom le, če mu ne sledijo črke "
"<literal>amp;</literal>, je videti takole: <literal>&amp;(?!amp;)</literal>. "
"To je seveda lažje brati z uporabo urejevalnika regularnih izrazov, kjer bi "
"uporabili <link linkend=\"lookaheadtools\">orodja lookahead</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Regular Expression Editor"
msgstr "Uporaba urejevalnika regularnih izrazov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter will tell you about how the regular expression editor works."
msgstr ""
"To poglavje vam bo povedalo, kako deluje urejevalnik regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "The organization of the screen"
msgstr "Organizacija zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most important part of the editor is of course the editing area, this is "
"the area where you draw your regular expression. This area is the larger "
"gray one in the middle."
msgstr ""
"Najpomembnejši del urejevalnika je seveda območje za urejanje, to je "
"področje, kjer narišete svoj regularni izraz. To območje je večje sivo na "
"sredini."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Above the editing area you have two Toolbars, the first one contains the "
"<link linkend=\"editingtools\">editing actions</link> - much like drawing "
"tools in a drawing program. The second Toolbar contains the <emphasis>What's "
"This?</emphasis> button, and buttons for undo and redo."
msgstr ""
"Nad območjem za urejanje imate dve orodni vrstici, prva vsebuje <link "
"linkend=\"editingtools\">urejevalna dejanja</link> - podobno kot orodja za "
"risanje v programu za risanje. Druga orodna vrstica vsebuje gumb "
"<emphasis>Kaj je to?</emphasis> ter gumba za razveljavitev in ponovitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below the editing area you find the regular expression currently build, in "
"the so called ascii syntax. The ascii syntax is updated while you edit the "
"regular expression in the graphical editor. If you rather want to update the "
"ascii syntax then please do, the graphical editor is updated on the fly to "
"reflect your changes."
msgstr ""
"Pod območjem za urejanje najdete trenutno zgrajen regularni izraz v tako "
"imenovani sintaksi ascii. Sintaksa ascii se posodobi, medtem ko urejate "
"regularni izraz v grafičnem urejevalniku. Če raje želite posodobiti sintakso "
"ascii, to storite, saj se grafični urejevalnik sproti posodablja, da odraža "
"vaše spremembe."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally to the left of the editor area you will find a number of pre-built "
"regular expressions. They serve two purposes: (1) When you load the editor "
"with a regular expression then this regular expression is made "
"<emphasis>nicer</emphasis> or more comprehensive by replacing common regular "
"expressions. In the screen dump above, you can see how the ascii syntax \".*"
"\" have been replaced with a box saying \"anything\". (2) When you insert "
"regular expression you may find building blocks for your own regular "
"expression from the set of pre build regular expressions. See the section on "
"<link linkend=\"userdefinedregexps\">user defined regular expressions</link> "
"to learn how to save your own regular expressions."
msgstr ""
"Končno na levi strani urejevalnika boste našli številne vnaprej izdelane "
"regularne izraze. Služijo dvema namenoma: (1) Ko naložite urejevalnik z "
"regularnim izrazom, je ta regularni izraz <emphasis>lepši</emphasis> ali "
"bolj celovit z zamenjavo običajnih regularnih izrazov. Na zgornjem izpisu "
"zaslona lahko vidite, kako je bila sintaksa ascii \".*\" nadomeščena s "
"poljem \"karkoli\". (2) Ko vstavite regularni izraz, boste morda našli "
"gradnike za lasten regularni izraz iz nabora regularnih izrazov, ki so bili "
"predhodno izdelani. Oglejte si razdelek o <link linkend=\"userdefinedregexps"
"\">uporabniško definiranih regularnih izrazih</link>, če želite izvedeti, "
"kako shranite lastne regularne izraze."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Tools"
msgstr "Orodja za urejanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text in this section expects that you have read the chapter on <link "
"linkend=\"whatIsARegExp\">what a regular expression is</link>, or have "
"previous knowledge on this subject."
msgstr ""
"Besedilo v tem razdelku pričakuje, da ste prebrali poglavje o <link linkend="
"\"whatIsARegExp\">kaj je regularni izraz</link> ali da imate predhodno "
"znanje o tej temi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All the editing tools are located in the toolbar above editing area. Each of "
"them will be described in the following."
msgstr ""
"Vsa orodja za urejanje se nahajajo v orodni vrstici nad območjem za "
"urejanje. Vsak od njih bo opisan v nadaljevanju."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selection Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za izbiro"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The selection tool is used to mark elements for cut-and-paste and drag-and-"
"drop. This is very similar to a selection tool in any drawing program."
msgstr ""
"Izbirno orodje se uporablja za označevanje elementov za izrezovanje in "
"lepljenje ter povleci in spusti. To je zelo podobno izbirnemu orodju v "
"katerem koli programu za risanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za besedilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this tool you will insert normal text to match. The text is matched "
"literally, &ie; you do not have to worry about escaping of special "
"characters. In the example above the following regular expression will be "
"build: <literal>abc\\*\\\\\\)</literal>"
msgstr ""
"S tem orodjem boste vstavili normalno besedilo, ki se bo ujemalo. Besedilo "
"se ujema dobesedno, &ie; ni vam treba skrbeti za uhajanje posebnih znakov. V "
"zgornjem primeru bo zgrajen naslednji regularni izraz: <literal>abc\\*\\\\"
"\\)</literal>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Character Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za znake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this tool you insert character ranges. Examples includes what in ASCII "
"text says <literal>[0-9]</literal>, <literal>[^a-zA-Z,_]</literal>. When "
"inserting an item with this tool a dialog will appear, in which you specify "
"the character ranges."
msgstr ""
"S tem orodjem vstavite obseg znakov. Primeri vključujejo tisto, kar v "
"besedilu ASCII piše <literal>[0-9]</literal>, <literal>[^a-zA-Z,_]</"
"literal>. Ko vstavite element s tem orodjem, se prikaže pogovorno okno, v "
"katerem določite obsege znakov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">repeated regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">ponavljajočih se regularnih "
"izrazov</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid "Any Character Tool"
msgstr "Poljubno orodje za znake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the regular expression \"dot\" (.). It matches any single character."
msgstr ""
"To je regularni izraz \"dot\" (.). Ujema se s katerim koli posameznim znakom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repeat Tool"
msgstr "Orodje za ponavljanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the repeated elements. This includes what in ASCII syntax is "
"represented using an asterix (*), a plus (+), a question mark (?), and "
"ranges ({3,5}). When you insert an item using this tool, a dialog will "
"appear asking for the number of times to repeat."
msgstr ""
"To so ponavljajoči se elementi. To vključuje tisto, kar je v sintaksi ASCII "
"predstavljeno z zvezdico (*), plusom (+), vprašajem (?) in obsegi ({3,5}). "
"Ko s tem orodjem vstavite element, se prikaže pogovorno okno, ki vas vpraša, "
"kolikokrat naj se ponovi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You specify what to repeat by drawing the repeated content inside the box "
"which this tool inserts."
msgstr ""
"Določite, kaj želite ponoviti, tako da narišete ponovljeno vsebino znotraj "
"polja, ki ga to orodje vstavi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Repeated elements can both be built from the outside in and the inside out. "
"That is you can first draw what to be repeated, select it and use the repeat "
"tool to repeat it. Alternatively you can first insert the repeat element, "
"and draw what is to be repeated inside it."
msgstr ""
"Ponavljajoče se elemente je mogoče zgraditi od zunaj navznoter in od znotraj "
"navzven. To pomeni, da lahko najprej narišete, kaj želite ponoviti, to "
"izberete in uporabite orodje za ponavljanje, da to ponovite. Druga možnost "
"je, da najprej vstavite ponavljajoči se element in znotraj njega narišete, "
"kar naj se ponovi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description on the <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">repeated regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">ponavljajočih se regularnih "
"izrazov</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternative Tool"
msgstr "Alternativno orodje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the alternative regular expression (|). You specify the alternatives "
"by drawing each alternative on top of each other inside the box that this "
"tool inserts."
msgstr ""
"To je alternativni regularni izraz (|). Nadomestne možnosti določite tako, "
"da vsako alternativno možnost narišete eno na drugo znotraj polja, ki ga "
"vstavi to orodje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description on <link linkend=\"altnregexp\">alternative regular "
"expressions</link>"
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"altnregexp\">alternativnih regularnih "
"izrazov</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compound Tool"
msgstr "Sestavljeno orodje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The compound tool does not represent any regular expressions. It is used to "
"group other sub parts together in a box, which easily can be collapsed to "
"only its title. This can be seen in the right part of the screen dump above."
msgstr ""
"Sestavljeno orodje ne predstavlja nobenih regularnih izrazov. Uporablja se "
"za združevanje drugih poddelov v okvir, ki ga je mogoče zlahka strniti samo "
"na naslov. To lahko vidite v desnem delu zgornjega izpisa zaslona."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line Start/End Tools"
msgstr "Orodja za začetek/konec vrstice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The line start and line end tools matches the start of the line, and the end "
"of the line respectively. The regular expression in the screen dump above "
"thus matches lines only matches spaces."
msgstr ""
"Orodja za začetek in konec vrstice se ujemajo z začetkom in koncem vrstice. "
"Regularni izraz v zgornjem izpisu zaslona se torej ujema s črtami in samo s "
"presledki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"positionregexp\">position regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"positionregexp\">regularnih izrazov "
"položaja</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Word (Non)Boundary Tools"
msgstr "Orodja za (ne)meje besed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The boundary tools matches a word boundary respectively a non-word boundary. "
"The regular expression in the screen dump thus matches any words starting "
"with <literal>the</literal>. The word <literal>the</literal> itself is, "
"however, not matched."
msgstr ""
"Orodja za meje se ujemajo z besedno mejo oziroma nebesedno mejo. Regularni "
"izraz v izpisu zaslona se tako ujema s katero koli besedo, ki se začne z "
"<literal>the</literal>. Sama beseda <literal>the</literal> pa se ne ujema."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"boundaryregexp\">boundary regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"boundaryregexp\">mejnih regularnih izrazov</"
"link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:519
#, no-c-format
msgid "Positive/Negative Lookahead Tools"
msgstr "Orodja za pozitivni/negativni pogled naprej"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The look ahead tools either specify a positive or negative regular "
"expression to match. The match is, however, not part of the total match."
msgstr ""
"Orodja za pogled naprej določajo pozitivni ali negativni regularni izraz za "
"ujemanje. Ujemanje pa ni del celotnega ujemanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note: You are only allowed to place lookaheads at the end of the regular "
"expressions. The Regular Expression Editor widget does not enforce this."
msgstr ""
"Opomba: na koncu regularnih izrazov lahko postavite samo pogled naprej. "
"Gradnik urejevalnika regularnih izrazov tega ne uveljavlja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"lookaheadregexp\">look ahead regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si opis <link linkend=\"lookaheadregexp\">regularnih izrazov za "
"pogled naprej</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:546
#, no-c-format
msgid "User Defined Regular Expressions"
msgstr "Uporabniško določeni regularni izrazi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:547
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Located at the left of the editing area is a list box containing user "
"defined regular expressions. Some regular expressions are pre-installed with "
"your &kde; installation, while others you can save yourself."
msgstr ""
"Na levi strani območja za urejanje je polje s seznamom, ki vsebuje "
"uporabniško določene regularne izraze. Nekateri regularni izrazi so vnaprej "
"nameščeni v vašem &kde; namestitev, druge pa lahko rešite sami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These regular expression serves two purposes (<link linkend="
"\"screenorganization\">see detailed description</link>), namely (1) to offer "
"you a set of building block and (2) to make common regular expressions "
"prettier."
msgstr ""
"Ti regularni izrazi imajo dva namena (<link linkend=\"screenorganization"
"\">glejte podroben opis</link>), in sicer (1) da vam ponudijo nabor "
"gradnikov in (2) da polepšajo običajne regularne izraze."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can save your own regular expressions by right clicking the mouse button "
"in the editing area, and choosing <literal>Save Regular Expression</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Lastne regularne izraze lahko shranite tako, da z desno miškino tipko "
"kliknete v območju za urejanje in izberete <literal>Shrani regularni izraz</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the regular expression you save is within a <link linkend=\"compoundtool"
"\">compound container</link> then the regular expression will take part in "
"making subsequent regular expressions prettier."
msgstr ""
"Če je regularni izraz, ki ga shranite, znotraj <link linkend=\"compoundtool"
"\">sestavljenega vsebnika</link>, bo regularni izraz sodeloval pri lepšanju "
"naslednjih regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"User defined regular expressions can be deleted or renamed by pressing the "
"right mouse button on top of the regular expression in question in the list "
"box."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniško definirane regularne izraze lahko izbrišete ali preimenujete "
"tako, da pritisnete desno miškino tipko na vrh zadevnega regularnega izraza "
"v polju s seznamom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting bugs and Suggesting Features"
msgstr "Poročanje o napakah in predlaganje funkcij"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bug reports and feature requests should be submitted through the <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">&kde; Bug Tracking System</ulink>. <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">Before</emphasis> you report a bug or suggest a feature, please "
"check that it hasn't already been <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/buglist."
"cgi?quicksearch=kregexpeditor\">reported/suggested.</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Poročila o napakah in zahteve po funkcijah je treba oddati prek <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">&kde; Sistem za sledenje napakam</ulink>. <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">Preden</emphasis> prijavite napako ali predlagate funkcijo, "
"preverite, ali ni že bila <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/buglist.cgi? "
"quicksearch=kregexpeditor\">prijavljen/predlagan.</ulink>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr "Pogosto zastavljena vprašanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does the regular expression editor support back references?"
msgstr "Ali urejevalnik regularnih izrazov podpira povratne reference?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:591
#, no-c-format
msgid "No currently this is not supported. It is planned for the next version."
msgstr "Ne, trenutno to ni podprto. Načrtovano je za naslednjo različico."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does the regular expression editor support showing matches?"
msgstr "Ali urejevalnik regularnih izrazov podpira prikaz ujemanj?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:597
#, no-c-format
msgid "No, hopefully this will be available in the next version."
msgstr "Ne, upajmo, da bo to na voljo v naslednji različici."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I'm the author of a &kde; program, how can I use this widget in my "
"application?"
msgstr ""
"Sem avtor &kde; programa, kako lahko uporabim ta pripomoček v svoji "
"aplikaciji?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org/documentation/library/cvs-api/"
"classref/interfaces/KRegExpEditorInterface.html\">The documentation for the "
"class KRegExpEditorInterface</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org/documentation/library/cvs-"
"api/classref/interfaces/KRegExpEditorInterface.html\">dokumentacijo za "
"razred KRegExpEditorInterface</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I cannot find the <emphasis>Edit Regular expression</emphasis> button in for "
"example konqueror on another KDE3 installation, why?"
msgstr ""
"Ne najdem gumba <emphasis>Uredi regularni izraz</emphasis> v na primer "
"konquerorju v drugi namestitvi KDE3, zakaj?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:610
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression widget is located in the package &kde;-utils. If you "
"do not have this package installed, then the <emphasis>edit regular "
"expressions</emphasis> buttons will not appear in the programs."
msgstr ""
"Gradnik regularnega izraza se nahaja v paketu &kde;-utils. Če tega paketa "
"nimate nameščenega, gumbi za <emphasis>urejanje regularnih izrazov</"
"emphasis> ne bodo prikazani v programih."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:621
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credits and License"
msgstr "Zasluge in licenca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Documentation is copyright 2001, Jesper K. Pedersen &Jesper.Pedersen.mail;"
msgstr ""
"Dokumentacija je avtorsko zaščitena 2001, Jesper K. Pedersen &Jesper."
"Pedersen.mail;"

